                # Decode a +string+ encoded in Punycode
        
      194. 
      
        
    194. 
          1
          
                def decode(string)
        
      195. 
      
        
    195. 
          
          
                  # Initialize the state
        
      196. 
      
        
    196. 
          
          
                  n = INITIAL_N
        
      197. 
      
        
    197. 
          
          
                  i = 0
        
      198. 
      
        
    198. 
          
          
                  bias = INITIAL_BIAS
        
      199. 
      
        
    199. 
          
          
          
        
      200. 
      
        
    200. 
          
          
                  if j = string.rindex(DELIMITER)
        
      201. 
      
        
    201. 
          
          
                    b = string[0...j]
        
      202. 
      
        
    202. 
          
          
          
        
      203. 
      
        
    203.

      204. 
      
        
    204.

      205. 
      
        
    205. 
          
          
          
        
      206. 
      
        
    206. 
          
          
                    # Handle the basic code points
        
      207. 
      
        
    207. 
          
          
          
        
      208. 
      
        
    208.

      209. 
      
        
    209. 
          
          
                    u = string[(j + 1)..-1]
        
      210. 
      
        
    210. 
          
          
                  else
        
      211. 
      
        
    211. 
          
          
                    output = []
        
      212. 
      
        
    212. 
          
          
                    u = string
        
      213. 
      
        
    213. 
          
          
                  end
        
      214. 
      
        
    214. 
          
          
          
        
      215. 
      
        
    215. 
          
          
                  # Main decoding loop: Start just after the last delimiter if any
        
      216. 
      
        
    216. 
          
          
                  # basic code points were copied; start at the beginning
        
      217. 
      
        
    217. 
          
          
                  # otherwise.
        
      218. 
      
        
    218. 
          
          
          
        
      219. 
      
        
    219.

      220. 
      
        
    220. 
          
          
                  input_length = input.length
        
      221. 
      
        
    221. 
          
          
                  h = 0
        
      222. 
      
        
    222. 
          
          
                  out = output.length
        
      223. 
      
        
    223. 
          
          
          
        
      224. 
      
        
    224. 
          
          
                  while h < input_length
        
      225. 
      
        
    225. 
          
          
                    # Decode a generalized variable-length integer into delta,
        
      226. 
      
        
    226. 
          
          
                    # which gets added to i.  The overflow checking is easier
        
      227. 
      
        
    227. 
          
          
                    # if we increase i as we go, then subtract off its starting
        
      228. 
      
        
    228. 
          
          
                    # value at the end to obtain delta.
        
      229. 
      
        
    229. 
          
          
          
        
      230.

                    oldi = i
        
      231. 
      
        
    231. 
          
          
                    w = 1
        
      232. 
      
        
    232. 
          
          
                    k = BASE
        
      233. 
      
        
    233. 
          
          
          
        
      234. 
      
        
    234. 
          
          
                    loop {
        
      235. 
      
        
    235. 
          
          
                      digit = DECODE_DIGIT[input[h]] or
        
      236. 
      
        
    236. 
          
          
                      raise ArgumentError, "Illegal character is found in non-basic part: #{string.inspect}"
        
      237. 
      
        
    237. 
          
          
                      h += 1
        
      238. 
      
        
    238.

      239. 
      
        
    239. 
          
          
                      raise BufferOverflowError if i > MAXINT
        
      240. 
      
        
    240. 
          
          
                      t = k <= bias ? TMIN : k - bias >= TMAX ? TMAX : k - bias
        
      241. 
      
        
    241. 
          
          
                      break if digit < t
        
      242. 
      
        
    242.

      243. 
      
        
    243. 
          
          
                      raise BufferOverflowError if w > MAXINT
        
      244. 
      
        
    244. 
          
          
                      k += BASE
        
      245. 
      
        
    245. 
          
          
                      h < input_length or raise ArgumentError, "Malformed input given: #{string.inspect}"
        
      246. 
      
        
    246. 
          
          
                    }
        
      247. 
      
        
    247. 
          
          
          
        
      248. 
      
        
    248. 
          
          
                    # Adapt the bias
        
      249. 
      
        
    249. 
          
          
                    delta = oldi == 0 ? i / DAMP : (i - oldi) >> 1
        
      250. 
      
        
    250. 
          
          
                    delta += delta / (out + 1)
        
      251. 
      
        
    251. 
          
          
                    bias = 0
        
      252. 
      
        
    252. 
          
          
                    while delta > CUTOFF
        
      253. 
      
        
    253. 
          
          
                      delta /= LOBASE
        
      254. 
      
        
    254. 
          
          
                      bias += BASE
        
      255. 
      
        
    255. 
          
          
                    end
        
      256. 
      
        
    256. 
          
          
                    bias += (LOBASE + 1) * delta / (delta + SKEW)
        
      257. 
      
        
    257. 
          
          
          
        
      258. 
      
        
    258. 
          
          
                    # i was supposed to wrap around from out+1 to 0, incrementing
        
      259. 
      
        
    259. 
          
          
                    # n each time, so we'll fix that now:
        
      260. 
      
        
    260. 
          
          
          
        
      261. 
      
        
    261. 
          
          
                    q, i = i.divmod(out + 1)
        
      262. 
      
        
    262. 
          
          
                    n += q
        
      263. 
      
        
    263. 
          
          
                    raise BufferOverflowError if n > MAXINT
        
      264. 
      
        
    264. 
          
          
          
        
      265. 
      
        
    265. 
          
          
                    # Insert n at position i of the output:
        
      266. 
      
        
    266. 
          
          
          
        
      267. 
      
        
    267. 
          
          
                    output[i, 0] = n
        
      268. 
      
        
    268. 
          
          
          
        
      269. 
      
        
    269. 
          
          
                    out += 1
        
      270. 
      
        
    270. 
          
          
                    i += 1
        
      271. 
      
        
    271. 
          
          
                  end
        
      272. 
      
        
    272. 
          
          
                  output.pack('U*')
        
      273. 
      
        
    273. 
          
          
                end
        
      274.

          module Hashie
        
      4. 
      
        
    4. 
          
          
            # Mash allows you to create pseudo-objects that have method-like
        
      5. 
      
        
    5. 
          
          
            # accessors for hash keys. This is useful for such implementations
        
      6. 
      
        
    6. 
          
          
            # as an API-accessing library that wants to fake robust objects
        
      7. 
      
        
    7. 
          
          
            # without the overhead of actually doing so. Think of it as OpenStruct
        
      8. 
      
        
    8. 
          
          
            # with some additional goodies.
        
      9. 
      
        
    9. 
          
          
            #
        
      10. 
      
        
    10. 
          
          
            # A Mash will look at the methods you pass it and perform operations
        
      11. 
      
        
    11. 
          
          
            # based on the following rules:
        
      12. 
      
        
    12. 
          
          
            #
        
      13. 
      
        
    13. 
          
          
            # * No punctuation: Returns the value of the hash for that key, or nil if none exists.
        
      14. 
      
        
    14. 
          
          
            # * Assignment (<tt>=</tt>): Sets the attribute of the given method name.
        
      15. 
      
        
    15. 
          
          
            # * Existence (<tt>?</tt>): Returns true or false depending on whether that key has been set.
        
      16. 
      
        
    16. 
          
          
            # * Bang (<tt>!</tt>): Forces the existence of this key, used for deep Mashes. Think of it as "touch" for mashes.
        
      17. 
      
        
    17. 
          
          
            # * Under Bang (<tt>_</tt>): Like Bang, but returns a new Mash rather than creating a key.  Used to test existance in deep Mashes.
        
      18. 
      
        
    18. 
          
          
            #
        
      19. 
      
        
    19.

    160. 
          
          
                case key ||= okey
        
      161. 
      
        
    161. 
          
          
                when :name
        
      162. 
      
        
    162. 
          
          
                  self.name = val
        
      163. 
      
        
    163. 
          
          
                when :value
        
      164. 
      
        
    164. 
          
          
                  value = val
        
      165. 
      
        
    165. 
          
          
                when :domain
        
      166. 
      
        
    166. 
          
          
                  domain = val
        
      167. 
      
        
    167. 
          
          
                when :path
        
      168. 
      
        
    168. 
          
          
                  self.path = val
        
      169. 
      
        
    169. 
          
          
                when :origin
        
      170. 
      
        
    170. 
          
          
                  origin = val
        
      171. 
      
        
    171. 
          
          
                when :for_domain, :for_domain?
        
      172. 
      
        
    172. 
          
          
                  for_domain = val
        
      173. 
      
        
    173. 
          
          
                when :max_age
        
      174. 
      
        
    174. 
          
          
                  # Let max_age take precedence over expires
        
      175. 
      
        
    175. 
          
          
                  max_age = val
        
      176. 
      
        
    176. 
          
          
                when :expires, :expires_at
        
      177. 
      
        
    177. 
          
          
                  self.expires = val unless max_age
        
      178. 
      
        
    178. 
          
          
                when :httponly, :httponly?
        
      179. 
      
        
    179. 
          
          
                  @httponly = val
        
      180. 
      
        
    180. 
          
          
                when :secure, :secure?
        
      181. 
      
        
    181. 
          
          
                  @secure = val
        
      182. 
      
        
    182. 
          
          
                when Symbol
        
      183. 
      
        
    183. 
          
          
                  setter = :"#{key}="
        
      184. 
      
        
    184. 
          
          
                  if respond_to?(setter)
        
      185. 
      
        
    185. 
          
          
                    __send__(setter, val)
        
      186. 
      
        
    186. 
          
          
                  else
        
      187. 
      
        
    187. 
          
          
                    warn "unknown attribute name: #{okey.inspect}" if $VERBOSE
        
      188. 
      
        
    188. 
          
          
                    next
        
      189. 
      
        
    189. 
          
          
                  end
        
      190. 
      
        
    190. 
          
          
                when String
        
      191. 
      
        
    191. 
          
          
                  warn "use downcased symbol for keyword: #{okey.inspect}" if $VERBOSE
        
      192. 
      
        
    192. 
          
          
                  key = key.downcase.to_sym
        
      193. 
      
        
    193. 
          
          
                  redo
        
      194. 
      
        
    194. 
          
          
                else
        
      195. 
      
        
    195. 
          
          
                  warn "invalid keyword ignored: #{okey.inspect}" if $VERBOSE
        
      196. 
      
        
    196. 
          
          
                  next
        
      197. 
      
        
    197. 
          
          
                end
        
      198. 
      
        
    198. 
          
          
              }
        
      199. 
      
        
    199. 
          
          
              if @name.nil?
        
      200. 
      
        
    200. 
          
          
                raise ArgumentError, "name must be specified"
        
      201. 
      
        
    201. 
          
          
              end
        
      202. 
      
        
    202. 
          
          
              @for_domain = for_domain
        
      203. 
      
        
    203. 
          
          
              self.domain = domain if domain
        
      204. 
      
        
    204. 
          
          
              self.origin = origin if origin
        
      205. 
      
        
    205. 
          
          
              self.max_age = max_age if max_age
        
      206. 
      
        
    206. 
          
          
              self.value = value.nil? && (@expires || @max_age) ? '' : value
        
      207. 
      
        
    207. 
          
          
            end
        
      208.

          1
          
            autoload :Scanner, 'http/cookie/scanner'

          1
          
            class << self
        
      212. 
      
        
    212. 
          
          
              # Tests if +target_path+ is under +base_path+ as described in RFC
        
      213. 
      
        
    213. 
          
          
              # 6265 5.1.4.  +base_path+ must be an absolute path.
        
      214. 
      
        
    214. 
          
          
              # +target_path+ may be empty, in which case it is treated as the
        
      215. 
      
        
    215. 
          
          
              # root path.
        
      216. 
      
        
    216. 
          
          
              #
        
      217. 
      
        
    217. 
          
          
              # e.g.
        
      218. 
      
        
    218. 
          
          
              #
        
      219. 
      
        
    219. 
          
          
              #         path_match?('/admin/', '/admin/index') == true
        
      220. 
      
        
    220. 
          
          
              #         path_match?('/admin/', '/Admin/index') == false
        
      221. 
      
        
    221. 
          
          
              #         path_match?('/admin/', '/admin/') == true
        
      222. 
      
        
    222. 
          
          
              #         path_match?('/admin/', '/admin') == false
        
      223. 
      
        
    223. 
          
          
              #
        
      224. 
      
        
    224. 
          
          
              #         path_match?('/admin', '/admin') == true
        
      225. 
      
        
    225. 
          
          
              #         path_match?('/admin', '/Admin') == false
        
      226. 
      
        
    226. 
          
          
              #         path_match?('/admin', '/admins') == false
        
      227. 
      
        
    227. 
          
          
              #         path_match?('/admin', '/admin/') == true
        
      228. 
      
        
    228. 
          
          
              #         path_match?('/admin', '/admin/index') == true
        
      229. 
      
        
    229. 
          1
          
              def path_match?(base_path, target_path)
        
      230. 
      
        
    230. 
          
          
                base_path.start_with?('/') or return false
        
      231. 
      
        
    231. 
          
          
                # RFC 6265 5.1.4
        
      232. 
      
        
    232. 
          
          
                bsize = base_path.size
        
      233. 
      
        
    233. 
          
          
                tsize = target_path.size
        
      234. 
      
        
    234. 
          
          
                return bsize == 1 if tsize == 0 # treat empty target_path as "/"
        
      235. 
      
        
    235. 
          
          
                return false unless target_path.start_with?(base_path)
        
      236. 
      
        
    236. 
          
          
                return true if bsize == tsize || base_path.end_with?('/')
        
      237. 
      
        
    237. 
          
          
                target_path[bsize] == ?/
        
      238. 
      
        
    238. 
          
          
              end
        
      239. 
      
        
    239. 
          
          
          
        
      240. 
      
        
    240. 
          
          
              # Parses a Set-Cookie header value `set_cookie` assuming that it
        
      241. 
      
        
    241. 
          
          
              # is sent from a source URI/URL `origin`, and returns an array of
        
      242. 
      
        
    242. 
          
          
              # Cookie objects.  Parts (separated by commas) that are malformed
        
      243. 
      
        
    243. 
          
          
              # or considered unacceptable are silently ignored.
        
      244. 
      
        
    244. 
          
          
              #
        
      245. 
      
        
    245. 
          
          
              # If a block is given, each cookie object is passed to the block.
        
      246. 
      
        
    246. 
          
          
              #
        
      247. 
      
        
    247. 
          
          
              # Available option keywords are below:
        
      248. 
      
        
    248. 
          
          
              #
        
      249. 
      
        
    249. 
          
          
              # :created_at
        
      250. 
      
        
    250. 
          
          
              # : The creation time of the cookies parsed.
        
      251. 
      
        
    251. 
          
          
              #
        
      252. 
      
        
    252. 
          
          
              # :logger
        
      253. 
      
        
    253. 
          
          
              # : Logger object useful for debugging
        
      254. 
      
        
    254. 
          
          
              #
        
      255. 
      
        
    255. 
          
          
              # ### Compatibility Note for Mechanize::Cookie users
        
      256. 
      
        
    256. 
          
          
              #
        
      257. 
      
        
    257. 
          
          
              # * Order of parameters changed in HTTP::Cookie.parse:
        
      258. 
      
        
    258. 
          
          
              #
        
      259. 
      
        
    259. 
          
          
              #         Mechanize::Cookie.parse(uri, set_cookie[, log])
        
      260. 
      
        
    260. 
          
          
              #
        
      261. 
      
        
    261. 
          
          
              #         HTTP::Cookie.parse(set_cookie, uri[, :logger => # log])
        
      262. 
      
        
    262. 
          
          
              #
        
      263. 
      
        
    263. 
          
          
              # * HTTP::Cookie.parse does not accept nil for `set_cookie`.
        
      264. 
      
        
    264. 
          
          
              #
        
      265. 
      
        
    265. 
          
          
              # * HTTP::Cookie.parse does not yield nil nor include nil in an
        
      266. 
      
        
    266. 
          
          
              #   returned array.  It simply ignores unparsable parts.
        
      267. 
      
        
    267. 
          
          
              #
        
      268. 
      
        
    268. 
          
          
              # * HTTP::Cookie.parse is made to follow RFC 6265 to the extent
        
      269. 
      
        
    269. 
          
          
              #   not terribly breaking interoperability with broken
        
      270. 
      
        
    270. 
          
          
              #   implementations.  In particular, it is capable of parsing
        
      271. 
      
        
    271. 
          
          
              #   cookie definitions containing double-quotes just as naturally
        
      272. 
      
        
    272. 
          
          
              #   expected.
        
      273. 
      
        
    273. 
          1
          
              def parse(set_cookie, origin, options = nil, &block)
        
      274. 
      
        
    274. 
          
          
                if options
        
      275. 
      
        
    275. 
          
          
                  logger = options[:logger]
        
      276. 
      
        
    276. 
          
          
                  created_at = options[:created_at]
        
      277. 
      
        
    277. 
          
          
                end
        
      278. 
      
        
    278. 
          
          
                origin = URI(origin)
        
      279. 
      
        
    279. 
          
          
          
        
      280. 
      
        
    280. 
          
          
                [].tap { |cookies|
        
      281. 
      
        
    281. 
          
          
                  Scanner.new(set_cookie, logger).scan_set_cookie { |name, value, attrs|
        
      282. 
      
        
    282. 
          
          
                    break if name.nil? || name.empty?
        
      283. 
      
        
    283. 
          
          
          
        
      284. 
      
        
    284. 
          
          
                    begin
        
      285. 
      
        
    285. 
          
          
                      cookie = new(name, value)
        
      286. 
      
        
    286. 
          
          
                    rescue => e
        
      287. 
      
        
    287. 
          
          
                      logger.warn("Invalid name or value: #{e}") if logger
        
      288. 
      
        
    288. 
          
          
                      next
        
      289. 
      
        
    289. 
          
          
                    end
        
      290. 
      
        
    290. 
          
          
                    cookie.created_at = created_at if created_at
        
      291. 
      
        
    291. 
          
          
                    attrs.each { |aname, avalue|
        
      292. 
      
        
    292. 
          
          
                      begin
        
      293. 
      
        
    293. 
          
          
                        case aname
        
      294. 
      
        
    294. 
          
          
                        when 'domain'
        
      295. 
      
        
    295. 
          
          
                          cookie.for_domain = true
        
      296. 
      
        
    296. 
          
          
                          # The following may negate @for_domain if the value is
        
      297. 
      
        
    297. 
          
          
                          # an eTLD or IP address, hence this order.
        
      298. 
      
        
    298. 
          
          
                          cookie.domain = avalue
        
      299. 
      
        
    299. 
          
          
                        when 'path'
        
      300. 
      
        
    300. 
          
          
                          cookie.path = avalue
        
      301. 
      
        
    301. 
          
          
                        when 'expires'
        
      302. 
      
        
    302. 
          
          
                          # RFC 6265 4.1.2.2
        
      303. 
      
        
    303. 
          
          
                          # The Max-Age attribute has precedence over the Expires
        
      304. 
      
        
    304. 
          
          
                          # attribute.
        
      305. 
      
        
    305. 
          
          
                          cookie.expires = avalue unless cookie.max_age
        
      306. 
      
        
    306. 
          
          
                        when 'max-age'
        
      307. 
      
        
    307. 
          
          
                          cookie.max_age = avalue
        
      308. 
      
        
    308. 
          
          
                        when 'secure'
        
      309. 
      
        
    309. 
          
          
                          cookie.secure = avalue
        
      310. 
      
        
    310. 
          
          
                        when 'httponly'
        
      311. 
      
        
    311. 
          
          
                          cookie.httponly = avalue
        
      312. 
      
        
    312. 
          
          
                        end
        
      313. 
      
        
    313. 
          
          
                      rescue => e
        
      314. 
      
        
    314. 
          
          
                        logger.warn("Couldn't parse #{aname} '#{avalue}': #{e}") if logger
        
      315. 
      
        
    315. 
          
          
                      end
        
      316. 
      
        
    316. 
          
          
                    }
        
      317. 
      
        
    317. 
          
          
          
        
      318. 
      
        
    318. 
          
          
                    cookie.origin = origin
        
      319. 
      
        
    319. 
          
          
          
        
      320. 
      
        
    320. 
          
          
                    cookie.acceptable? or next
        
      321. 
      
        
    321. 
          
          
          
        
      322. 
      
        
    322. 
          
          
                    yield cookie if block_given?
        
      323. 
      
        
    323. 
          
          
          
        
      324. 
      
        
    324. 
          
          
                    cookies << cookie
        
      325. 
      
        
    325. 
          
          
                  }
        
      326. 
      
        
    326. 
          
          
                }
        
      327. 
      
        
    327. 
          
          
              end
        
      328. 
      
        
    328. 
          
          
          
        
      329. 
      
        
    329. 
          
          
              # Takes an array of cookies and returns a string for use in the
        
      330. 
      
        
    330. 
          
          
              # Cookie header, like "name1=value2; name2=value2".
        
      331. 
      
        
    331. 
          1
          
              def cookie_value(cookies)
        
      332. 
      
        
    332. 
          
          
                cookies.join('; ')
        
      333. 
      
        
    333. 
          
          
              end
        
      334. 
      
        
    334. 
          
          
          
        
      335. 
      
        
    335. 
          
          
              # Parses a Cookie header value into a hash of name-value string
        
      336. 
      
        
    336. 
          
          
              # pairs.  The first appearance takes precedence if multiple pairs
        
      337. 
      
        
    337. 
          
          
              # with the same name occur.
        
      338. 
      
        
    338. 
          1
          
              def cookie_value_to_hash(cookie_value)
        
      339. 
      
        
    339. 
          
          
                {}.tap { |hash|
        
      340. 
      
        
    340. 
          
          
                  Scanner.new(cookie_value).scan_cookie { |name, value|
        
      341. 
      
        
    341. 
          
          
                    hash[name] ||= value
        
      342. 
      
        
    342. 
          
          
                  }
        
      343. 
      
        
    343. 
          
          
                }
        
      344. 
      
        
    344. 
          
          
              end
        
      345. 
      
        
    345. 
          
          
            end
        
      346. 
      
        
    346. 
          
          
          
        
      347. 
      
        
    347. 
          1
          
            attr_reader :name
        
      348. 
      
        
    348. 
          
          
          
        
      349. 
      
        
    349. 
          
          
            # See #name.
        
      350. 
      
        
    350. 
          1
          
            def name= name
        
      351. 
      
        
    351. 
          
          
              name = (String.try_convert(name) or
        
      352. 
      
        
    352. 
          
          
                raise TypeError, "#{name.class} is not a String")
        
      353. 
      
        
    353. 
          
          
              if name.empty?
        
      354. 
      
        
    354. 
          
          
                raise ArgumentError, "cookie name cannot be empty"
        
      355. 
      
        
    355. 
          
          
              elsif name.match(/[\x00-\x20\x7F,;\\"=]/)
        
      356. 
      
        
    356. 
          
          
                raise ArgumentError, "invalid cookie name"
        
      357. 
      
        
    357. 
          
          
              end
        
      358. 
      
        
    358. 
          
          
              # RFC 6265 4.1.1
        
      359. 
      
        
    359. 
          
          
              # cookie-name may not match:
        
      360. 
      
        
    360. 
          
          
              # /[\x00-\x20\x7F()<>@,;:\\"\/\[\]?={}]/
        
      361. 
      
        
    361. 
          
          
              @name = name
        
      362. 
      
        
    362. 
          
          
            end
        
      363. 
      
        
    363. 
          
          
          
        
      364. 
      
        
    364. 
          1
          
            attr_reader :value
        
      365. 
      
        
    365. 
          
          
          
        
      366. 
      
        
    366. 
          
          
            # See #value.
        
      367. 
      
        
    367. 
          1
          
            def value= value
        
      368. 
      
        
    368. 
          
          
              if value.nil?
        
      369. 
      
        
    369. 
          
          
                self.expires = UNIX_EPOCH
        
      370. 
      
        
    370. 
          
          
                return @value = ''
        
      371. 
      
        
    371. 
          
          
              end
        
      372. 
      
        
    372. 
          
          
              value = (String.try_convert(value) or
        
      373. 
      
        
    373. 
          
          
                raise TypeError, "#{value.class} is not a String")
        
      374. 
      
        
    374. 
          
          
              if value.match(/[\x00-\x1F\x7F]/)
        
      375. 
      
        
    375. 
          
          
                raise ArgumentError, "invalid cookie value"
        
      376. 
      
        
    376. 
          
          
              end
        
      377. 
      
        
    377. 
          
          
              # RFC 6265 4.1.1
        
      378. 
      
        
    378. 
          
          
              # cookie-name may not match:
        
      379. 
      
        
    379. 
          
          
              # /[^\x21\x23-\x2B\x2D-\x3A\x3C-\x5B\x5D-\x7E]/
        
      380. 
      
        
    380. 
          
          
              @value = value
        
      381. 
      
        
    381. 
          
          
            end
        
      382. 
      
        
    382. 
          
          
          
        
      383. 
      
        
    383. 
          1
          
            attr_reader :domain
        
      384. 
      
        
    384. 
          
          
          
        
      385. 
      
        
    385. 
          
          
            # See #domain.
        
      386. 
      
        
    386. 
          1
          
            def domain= domain
        
      387. 
      
        
    387. 
          
          
              case domain
        
      388. 
      
        
    388. 
          
          
              when nil
        
      389. 
      
        
    389. 
          
          
                @for_domain = false
        
      390. 
      
        
    390. 
          
          
                if @origin
        
      391. 
      
        
    391. 
          
          
                  @domain_name = DomainName.new(@origin.host)
        
      392. 
      
        
    392. 
          
          
                  @domain = @domain_name.hostname
        
      393. 
      
        
    393. 
          
          
                else
        
      394. 
      
        
    394. 
          
          
                  @domain_name = @domain = nil
        
      395. 
      
        
    395. 
          
          
                end
        
      396. 
      
        
    396. 
          
          
                return nil
        
      397. 
      
        
    397. 
          
          
              when DomainName
        
      398. 
      
        
    398. 
          
          
                @domain_name = domain
        
      399. 
      
        
    399. 
          
          
              else
        
      400. 
      
        
    400. 
          
          
                domain = (String.try_convert(domain) or
        
      401. 
      
        
    401. 
          
          
                  raise TypeError, "#{domain.class} is not a String")
        
      402. 
      
        
    402. 
          
          
                if domain.start_with?('.')
        
      403. 
      
        
    403. 
          
          
                  for_domain = true
        
      404. 
      
        
    404. 
          
          
                  domain = domain[1..-1]
        
      405. 
      
        
    405. 
          
          
                end
        
      406. 
      
        
    406. 
          
          
                if domain.empty?
        
      407. 
      
        
    407. 
          
          
                  return self.domain = nil
        
      408. 
      
        
    408. 
          
          
                end
        
      409. 
      
        
    409. 
          
          
                # Do we really need to support this?
        
      410. 
      
        
    410. 
          
          
                if domain.match(/\A([^:]+):[0-9]+\z/)
        
      411. 
      
        
    411. 
          
          
                  domain = $1
        
      412. 
      
        
    412. 
          
          
                end
        
      413. 
      
        
    413. 
          
          
                @domain_name = DomainName.new(domain)
        
      414. 
      
        
    414. 
          
          
              end
        
      415. 
      
        
    415. 
          
          
              # RFC 6265 5.3 5.
        
      416. 
      
        
    416. 
          
          
              if domain_name.domain.nil? # a public suffix or IP address
        
      417. 
      
        
    417. 
          
          
                @for_domain = false
        
      418. 
      
        
    418. 
          
          
              else
        
      419. 
      
        
    419. 
          
          
                @for_domain = for_domain unless for_domain.nil?
        
      420. 
      
        
    420. 
          
          
              end
        
      421. 
      
        
    421. 
          
          
              @domain = @domain_name.hostname
        
      422. 
      
        
    422. 
          
          
            end
        
      423. 
      
        
    423. 
          
          
          
        
      424. 
      
        
    424. 
          
          
            # Returns the domain, with a dot prefixed only if the domain flag is
        
      425. 
      
        
    425. 
          
          
            # on.
        
      426. 
      
        
    426. 
          1
          
            def dot_domain
        
      427. 
      
        
    427. 
          
          
              @for_domain ? '.' << @domain : @domain

            # is done against the lowercase version of the MIME::Type.
        
      128. 
      
        
    128. 
          1
          
            def <=>(other)
        
      129. 
      
        
    129. 
          4274
          
              if other.nil?
        
      130. 
      
        
    130. 
          
          
                -1
        
      131. 
      
        
    131. 
          4274
          
              elsif other.respond_to?(:simplified)
        
      132. 
      
        
    132. 
          
          
                simplified <=> other.simplified
        
      133. 
      
        
    133. 
          
          
              else
        
      134. 
      
        
    134. 
          4274
          
                filtered = 'silent' if other == :silent
        
      135. 
      
        
    135. 
          4274
          
                filtered ||= 'true' if other == true
        
      136. 
      
        
    136. 
          4274
          
                filtered ||= other.to_s
        
      137. 
      
        
    137. 
          
          
          
        
      138. 
      
        
    138. 
          4274
          
                simplified <=> MIME::Type.simplified(filtered)
        
      139. 
      
        
    139. 
          
          
              end
        
      140. 
      
        
    140. 
          
          
            end
        
      141. 
      
        
    141. 
          
          
          
        
      142. 
      
        
    142. 
          
          
            # Compares the +other+ MIME::Type based on how reliable it is before doing a
        
      143. 
      
        
    143. 
          
          
            # normal <=> comparison. Used by MIME::Types#[] to sort types. The
        
      144. 
      
        
    144. 
          
          
            # comparisons involved are:
        
      145. 
      
        
    145. 
          
          
            #
        
      146. 
      
        
    146. 
          
          
            # 1. self.simplified <=> other.simplified (ensures that we
        
      147. 
      
        
    147. 
          
          
            #    don't try to compare different types)
        
      148. 
      
        
    148. 
          
          
            # 2. IANA-registered definitions < other definitions.
        
      149. 
      
        
    149. 
          
          
            # 3. Complete definitions < incomplete definitions.
        
      150. 
      
        
    150. 
          
          
            # 4. Current definitions < obsolete definitions.
        
      151. 
      
        
    151. 
          
          
            # 5. Obselete with use-instead names < obsolete without.
        
      152. 
      
        
    152. 
          
          
            # 6. Obsolete use-instead definitions are compared.
        
      153. 
      
        
    153. 
          
          
            #
        
      154. 
      
        
    154. 
          
          
            # While this method is public, its use is strongly discouraged by consumers
        
      155. 
      
        
    155. 
          
          
            # of mime-types. In mime-types 3, this method is likely to see substantial
        
      156. 
      
        
    156. 
          
          
            # revision and simplification to ensure current registered content types sort
        
      157. 
      
        
    157. 
          
          
            # before unregistered or obsolete content types.
        
      158. 
      
        
    158. 
          1
          
            def priority_compare(other)
        
      159. 
      
        
    159. 
          
          
              pc = simplified <=> other.simplified
        
      160. 
      
        
    160. 
          
          
              if pc.zero? || !(extensions & other.extensions).empty?
        
      161. 
      
        
    161. 
          
          
                pc = if (reg = registered?) != other.registered?
        
      162. 
      
        
    162. 
          
          
                       reg ? -1 : 1 # registered < unregistered
        
      163. 
      
        
    163. 
          
          
                     elsif (comp = complete?) != other.complete?
        
      164. 
      
        
    164. 
          
          
                       comp ? -1 : 1 # complete < incomplete
        
      165. 
      
        
    165. 
          
          
                     elsif (obs = obsolete?) != other.obsolete?
        
      166. 
      
        
    166. 
          
          
                       obs ? 1 : -1 # current < obsolete
        
      167. 
      
        
    167. 
          
          
                     elsif obs and ((ui = use_instead) != (oui = other.use_instead))
        
      168. 
      
        
    168. 
          
          
                       if ui.nil?
        
      169. 
      
        
    169. 
          
          
                         1
        
      170. 
      
        
    170. 
          
          
                       elsif oui.nil?
        
      171. 
      
        
    171. 
          
          
                         -1
        
      172. 
      
        
    172. 
          
          
                       else
        
      173. 
      
        
    173. 
          
          
                         ui <=> oui
        
      174. 
      
        
    174. 
          
          
                       end
        
      175. 
      
        
    175. 
          
          
                     else
        
      176. 
      
        
    176. 
          
          
                       0
        
      177. 
      
        
    177. 
          
          
                     end
        
      178. 
      
        
    178. 
          
          
              end
        
      179. 
      
        
    179. 
          
          
          
        
      180. 
      
        
    180. 
          
          
              pc
        
      181. 
      
        
    181. 
          
          
            end
        
      182. 
      
        
    182. 
          
          
          
        
      183. 
      
        
    183.

    19. 
          
          
          # is required (<tt>require 'mime/types'</tt>), but it may be lazily loaded
        
      20. 
      
        
    20. 
          
          
          # (loaded on first use) with the use of the environment variable
        
      21. 
      
        
    21. 
          
          
          # +RUBY_MIME_TYPES_LAZY_LOAD+ having any value other than +false+. The
        
      22. 
      
        
    22. 
          
          
          # initial startup is about 14 faster (~10 ms vs ~140 ms), but the
        
      23. 
      
        
    23. 
          
          
          # registry will be loaded at some point in the future.
        
      24. 
      
        
    24. 
          
          
          #
        
      25. 
      
        
    25. 
          
          
          # The default mime-types registry can also be loaded from a Marshal cache
        
      26. 
      
        
    26. 
          
          
          # file specific to the version of MIME::Types being loaded. This will be
        
      27. 
      
        
    27. 
          
          
          # handled automatically with the use of a file referred to in the
        
      28. 
      
        
    28. 
          
          
          # environment variable +RUBY_MIME_TYPES_CACHE+. MIME::Types will attempt to
        
      29. 
      
        
    29. 
          
          
          # load the registry from this cache file (MIME::Type::Cache.load); if it
        
      30. 
      
        
    30. 
          
          
          # cannot be loaded (because the file does not exist, there is an error, or
        
      31. 
      
        
    31. 
          
          
          # the data is for a different version of mime-types), the default registry
        
      32.

          # will be loaded from the normal JSON version and then the cache file will
        
      33.

          # be *written* to the location indicated by +RUBY_MIME_TYPES_CACHE+. Cache
        
      34.

      35. 
      
        
    35. 
          
          
          # loads.
        
      36. 
      
        
    36.

      37. 
      
        
    37. 
          
          
          # Notes:
        
      38. 
      
        
    38. 
          
          
          # * The loading of the default registry is *not* atomic; when using a
        
      39.

          #   multi-threaded environment, it is recommended that lazy loading is not
        
      40. 
      
        
    40. 
          
          
          #   used and mime-types is loaded as early as possible.
        
      41. 
      
        
    41. 
          
          
          # * Cache files should be specified per application in a multiprocess
        
      42. 
      
        
    42. 
          
          
          #   environment and should be initialized during deployment or before
        
      43. 
      
        
    43. 
          
          
          #   forking to minimize the chance that the multiple processes will be
        
      44.

      45.

      46.

      47.

      48.

              def record result # :nodoc:
        
      666.

          1

          1
          
                self.assertions += result.assertions

      669. 
      
        
    669. 
          1
          
                results << result if not result.passed? or result.skipped?
        
      670. 
      
        
    670.

      672.

              def report # :nodoc:
        
      673. 
      
        
    673. 
          1
          
                aggregate = results.group_by { |r| r.failure.class }

    674. 
          1
          
                aggregate.default = [] # dumb. group_by should provide this
        
      675. 
      
        
    675.

          1

          1

    678. 
          1

      679. 
      
        
    679. 
          1
          
                self.skips      = aggregate[Skip].size
        
      680. 
      
        
    680. 
          
          
              end

    110. 
          
          
                if defined? Encoding then
        
      111. 
      
        
    111. 
          
          
                  s = s.encode Encoding.default_external
        
      112. 
      
        
    112. 
          
          
          
        
      113. 
      
        
    113. 
          
          
                  if String === obj && obj.encoding != Encoding.default_external then
        
      114. 
      
        
    114. 
          
          
                    s = "# encoding: #{obj.encoding}\n#{s}"
        
      115. 
      
        
    115.

      116. 
      
        
    116. 
          
          
                end

              ##
        
      122. 
      
        
    122. 
          
          
              # This returns a diff-able human-readable version of +obj+. This
        
      123. 
      
        
    123. 
          
          
              # differs from the regular mu_pp because it expands escaped
        
      124. 
      
        
    124. 
          
          
              # newlines and makes hex-values generic (like object_ids). This
        
      125. 
      
        
    125. 
          
          
              # uses mu_pp to do the first pass and then cleans it up.
        
      126. 
      
        
    126. 
          
          
          
        
      127. 
      
        
    127. 
          1
          
              def mu_pp_for_diff obj
        
      128. 
      
        
    128. 
          
          
                mu_pp(obj).gsub(/\\n/, "\n").gsub(/:0x[a-fA-F0-9]{4,}/m, ":0xXXXXXX")
        
      129. 
      
        
    129. 
          
          
              end

              def assert test, msg = nil
        
      135. 
      
        
    135. 
          2
          
                self.assertions += 1
        
      136. 
      
        
    136. 
          2
          
                unless test then
        
      137. 
      
        
    137. 
          
          
                  msg ||= "Expected #{mu_pp test} to be truthy."
        
      138. 
      
        
    138. 
          
          
                  msg = msg.call if Proc === msg
        
      139. 
      
        
    139. 
          
          
                  raise Minitest::Assertion, msg
        
      140. 
      
        
    140. 
          
          
                end
        
      141. 
      
        
    141. 
          2
          
                true
        
      142. 
      
        
    142. 
          
          
              end
        
      143.

      161. 
      
        
    161.

      162.

      163.

      164.

      165. 
      
        
    165.

      166. 
      
        
    166. 
          
          
              # Minitest::Test.make_my_diffs_pretty!
        
      167.

      168.

              # For floats use assert_in_delta.

      171.

      172. 
      
        
    172. 
          1
          
              def assert_equal exp, act, msg = nil
        
      173. 
      
        
    173. 
          1
          
                msg = message(msg, E) { diff exp, act }
        
      174. 
      
        
    174. 
          1
          
                result = assert exp == act, msg
        
      175. 
      
        
    175. 
          
          
          
        
      176. 
      
        
    176. 
          1
          
                if nil == exp then
        
      177. 
      
        
    177. 
          
          
                  if Minitest::VERSION =~ /^6/ then
        
      178. 
      
        
    178. 
          
          
                    refute_nil exp, "Use assert_nil if expecting nil."
        
      179. 
      
        
    179. 
          
          
                  else
        
      180. 
      
        
    180. 
          
          
                    where = Minitest.filter_backtrace(caller).first
        
      181. 
      
        
    181. 
          
          
                    where = where.split(/:in /, 2).first # clean up noise
        
      182. 
      
        
    182. 
          
          
          
        
      183. 
      
        
    183. 
          
          
                    warn "DEPRECATED: Use assert_nil if expecting nil from #{where}. This will fail in Minitest 6."
        
      184. 
      
        
    184. 
          
          
                  end
        
      185. 
      
        
    185. 
          
          
                end
        
      186. 
      
        
    186. 
          
          
          
        
      187. 
      
        
    187. 
          1
          
                result
        
      188.

              ##

    191. 
          
          
              # For comparing Floats.  Fails unless +exp+ and +act+ are within +delta+
        
      192.

      193.

    196. 
          1
          
              def assert_in_delta exp, act, delta = 0.001, msg = nil
        
      197. 
      
        
    197. 
          
          
                n = (exp - act).abs
        
      198. 
      
        
    198. 
          
          
                msg = message(msg) {
        
      199. 
      
        
    199. 
          
          
                  "Expected |#{exp} - #{act}| (#{n}) to be <= #{delta}"
        
      200. 
      
        
    200.

      201.

                assert delta >= n, msg
        
      202. 
      
        
    202. 
          
          
              end

              ##

    274. 
          
          
              # Fails if stdout or stderr do not output the expected results.

              # Pass in nil if you don't care about that streams output. Pass in
        
      276.

      277.

              # NOTE: this uses #capture_io, not #capture_subprocess_io.

          1
          
              def assert_output stdout = nil, stderr = nil
        
      286. 
      
        
    286. 
          
          
                out, err = capture_io do
        
      287. 
      
        
    287. 
          
          
                  yield
        
      288. 
      
        
    288. 
          
          
                end
        
      289. 
      
        
    289. 
          
          
          
        
      290. 
      
        
    290. 
          
          
                err_msg = Regexp === stderr ? :assert_match : :assert_equal if stderr
        
      291.

                out_msg = Regexp === stdout ? :assert_match : :assert_equal if stdout
        
      292. 
      
        
    292. 
          
          
          
        
      293. 
      
        
    293. 
          
          
                y = send err_msg, stderr, err, "In stderr" if err_msg
        
      294. 
      
        
    294. 
          
          
                x = send out_msg, stdout, out, "In stdout" if out_msg
        
      295. 
      
        
    295. 
          
          
          
        
      296. 
      
        
    296. 
          
          
                (!stdout || x) && (!stderr || y)
        
      297. 
      
        
    297. 
          
          
              end
        
      298.

              ##
        
      314. 
      
        
    314. 
          
          
              # Fails unless the block raises one of +exp+. Returns the
        
      315.

              # exception matched so you can check the message, attributes, etc.
        
      316.

              # +exp+ takes an optional message on the end to help explain

      319. 
      
        
    319. 
          
          
              # passed.
        
      320.

      321. 
      
        
    321. 
          1
          
              def assert_raises *exp
        
      322. 
      
        
    322. 
          
          
                msg = "#{exp.pop}.\n" if String === exp.last
        
      323. 
      
        
    323. 
          
          
                exp << StandardError if exp.empty?
        
      324. 
      
        
    324. 
          
          
          
        
      325. 
      
        
    325. 
          
          
                begin
        
      326. 
      
        
    326. 
          
          
                  yield
        
      327. 
      
        
    327. 
          
          
                rescue *exp => e
        
      328. 
      
        
    328. 
          
          
                  pass # count assertion
        
      329. 
      
        
    329. 
          
          
                  return e
        
      330. 
      
        
    330. 
          
          
                rescue Minitest::Skip, Minitest::Assertion
        
      331. 
      
        
    331. 
          
          
                  # don't count assertion
        
      332. 
      
        
    332. 
          
          
                  raise
        
      333. 
      
        
    333.

      334.

    336. 
          
          
                  flunk proc {
        
      337. 
      
        
    337. 
          
          
                    exception_details(e, "#{msg}#{mu_pp(exp)} exception expected, not")
        
      338. 
      
        
    338. 
          
          
                  }
        
      339. 
      
        
    339. 
          
          
                end
        
      340. 
      
        
    340. 
          
          
          
        
      341. 
      
        
    341. 
          
          
                exp = exp.first if exp.size == 1
        
      342. 
      
        
    342. 
          
          
          
        
      343. 
      
        
    343. 
          
          
                flunk "#{msg}#{mu_pp(exp)} expected but nothing was raised."
        
      344. 
      
        
    344. 
          
          
              end
        
      345.

      346.

              ##

    368. 
          
          
              # +send_ary+ is a receiver, message and arguments.
        
      369. 
      
        
    369. 
          
          
              #
        
      370. 
      
        
    370. 
          
          
              # Fails unless the call returns a true value
        
      371.

    372. 
          1
          
              def assert_send send_ary, m = nil
        
      373. 
      
        
    373. 
          
          
                where = Minitest.filter_backtrace(caller).first
        
      374. 
      
        
    374. 
          
          
                where = where.split(/:in /, 2).first # clean up noise
        
      375.
