                warn "DEPRECATED: assert_send. From #{where}"
        
      376. 
      
        
    376. 
          
          
          
        
      377. 
      
        
    377. 
          
          
                recv, msg, *args = send_ary
        
      378. 
      
        
    378. 
          
          
                m = message(m) {
        
      379. 
      
        
    379. 
          
          
                  "Expected #{mu_pp(recv)}.#{msg}(*#{mu_pp(args)}) to return true" }
        
      380. 
      
        
    380. 
          
          
                assert recv.__send__(msg, *args), m
        
      381. 
      
        
    381. 
          
          
              end
        
      382. 
      
        
    382. 
          
          
          
        
      383. 
      
        
    383. 
          
          
              ##
        
      384. 
      
        
    384. 
          
          
              # Fails if the block outputs anything to stderr or stdout.
        
      385. 
      
        
    385. 
          
          
              #
        
      386. 
      
        
    386. 
          
          
              # See also: #assert_output
        
      387. 
      
        
    387. 
          
          
          
        
      388. 
      
        
    388. 
          1
          
              def assert_silent
        
      389. 
      
        
    389. 
          
          
                assert_output "", "" do
        
      390. 
      
        
    390. 
          
          
                  yield
        
      391. 
      
        
    391. 
          
          
                end
        
      392. 
      
        
    392. 
          
          
              end
        
      393. 
      
        
    393. 
          
          
          
        
      394. 
      
        
    394. 
          
          
              ##
        
      395. 
      
        
    395. 
          
          
              # Fails unless the block throws +sym+
        
      396. 
      
        
    396. 
          
          
          
        
      397. 
      
        
    397. 
          1
          
              def assert_throws sym, msg = nil
        
      398. 
      
        
    398. 
          
          
                default = "Expected #{mu_pp(sym)} to have been thrown"
        
      399. 
      
        
    399. 
          
          
                caught = true
        
      400. 
      
        
    400. 
          
          
                catch(sym) do
        
      401. 
      
        
    401. 
          
          
                  begin
        
      402. 
      
        
    402. 
          
          
                    yield
        
      403. 
      
        
    403. 
          
          
                  rescue ThreadError => e       # wtf?!? 1.8 + threads == suck
        
      404. 
      
        
    404. 
          
          
                    default += ", not \:#{e.message[/uncaught throw \`(\w+?)\'/, 1]}"
        
      405. 
      
        
    405. 
          
          
                  rescue ArgumentError => e     # 1.9 exception
        
      406. 
      
        
    406. 
          
          
                    raise e unless e.message.include?("uncaught throw")
        
      407. 
      
        
    407. 
          
          
                    default += ", not #{e.message.split(/ /).last}"
        
      408. 
      
        
    408. 
          
          
                  rescue NameError => e         # 1.8 exception
        
      409. 
      
        
    409. 
          
          
                    raise e unless e.name == sym
        
      410. 
      
        
    410. 
          
          
                    default += ", not #{e.name.inspect}"
        
      411. 
      
        
    411. 
          
          
                  end
        
      412. 
      
        
    412. 
          
          
                  caught = false
        
      413. 
      
        
    413. 
          
          
                end
        
      414. 
      
        
    414. 
          
          
          
        
      415. 
      
        
    415. 
          
          
                assert caught, message(msg) { default }
        
      416. 
      
        
    416. 
          
          
              end
        
      417. 
      
        
    417. 
          
          
          
        
      418. 
      
        
    418. 
          
          
              ##
        
      419. 
      
        
    419. 
          
          
              # Captures $stdout and $stderr into strings:
        
      420. 
      
        
    420. 
          
          
              #
        
      421. 
      
        
    421. 
          
          
              #   out, err = capture_io do
        
      422. 
      
        
    422. 
          
          
              #     puts "Some info"
        
      423. 
      
        
    423. 
          
          
              #     warn "You did a bad thing"
        
      424. 
      
        
    424. 
          
          
              #   end
        
      425. 
      
        
    425. 
          
          
              #
        
      426. 
      
        
    426. 
          
          
              #   assert_match %r%info%, out
        
      427. 
      
        
    427. 
          
          
              #   assert_match %r%bad%, err
        
      428. 
      
        
    428. 
          
          
              #
        
      429. 
      
        
    429. 
          
          
              # NOTE: For efficiency, this method uses StringIO and does not
        
      430. 
      
        
    430. 
          
          
              # capture IO for subprocesses. Use #capture_subprocess_io for
        
      431. 
      
        
    431. 
          
          
              # that.
        
      432. 
      
        
    432. 
          
          
          
        
      433. 
      
        
    433. 
          1
          
              def capture_io
        
      434. 
      
        
    434. 
          
          
                _synchronize do
        
      435. 
      
        
    435. 
          
          
                  begin
        
      436. 
      
        
    436. 
          
          
                    captured_stdout, captured_stderr = StringIO.new, StringIO.new
        
      437. 
      
        
    437. 
          
          
          
        
      438. 
      
        
    438. 
          
          
                    orig_stdout, orig_stderr = $stdout, $stderr
        
      439. 
      
        
    439. 
          
          
                    $stdout, $stderr         = captured_stdout, captured_stderr
        
      440. 
      
        
    440. 
          
          
          
        
      441. 
      
        
    441. 
          
          
                    yield
        
      442. 
      
        
    442. 
          
          
          
        
      443. 
      
        
    443. 
          
          
                    return captured_stdout.string, captured_stderr.string
        
      444. 
      
        
    444. 
          
          
                  ensure
        
      445. 
      
        
    445. 
          
          
                    $stdout = orig_stdout
        
      446. 
      
        
    446. 
          
          
                    $stderr = orig_stderr
        
      447. 
      
        
    447. 
          
          
                  end
        
      448. 
      
        
    448. 
          
          
                end
        
      449. 
      
        
    449. 
          
          
              end
        
      450. 
      
        
    450. 
          
          
          
        
      451. 
      
        
    451. 
          
          
              ##
        
      452. 
      
        
    452. 
          
          
              # Captures $stdout and $stderr into strings, using Tempfile to
        
      453. 
      
        
    453. 
          
          
              # ensure that subprocess IO is captured as well.
        
      454. 
      
        
    454. 
          
          
              #
        
      455. 
      
        
    455. 
          
          
              #   out, err = capture_subprocess_io do
        
      456. 
      
        
    456. 
          
          
              #     system "echo Some info"
        
      457. 
      
        
    457. 
          
          
              #     system "echo You did a bad thing 1>&2"
        
      458. 
      
        
    458. 
          
          
              #   end
        
      459. 
      
        
    459. 
          
          
              #
        
      460. 
      
        
    460. 
          
          
              #   assert_match %r%info%, out
        
      461. 
      
        
    461. 
          
          
              #   assert_match %r%bad%, err
        
      462. 
      
        
    462. 
          
          
              #
        
      463. 
      
        
    463. 
          
          
              # NOTE: This method is approximately 10x slower than #capture_io so
        
      464. 
      
        
    464. 
          
          
              # only use it when you need to test the output of a subprocess.
        
      465. 
      
        
    465. 
          
          
          
        
      466. 
      
        
    466. 
          1
          
              def capture_subprocess_io
        
      467. 
      
        
    467. 
          
          
                _synchronize do
        
      468. 
      
        
    468. 
          
          
                  begin
        
      469. 
      
        
    469. 
          
          
                    require "tempfile"
        
      470. 
      
        
    470. 
          
          
          
        
      471. 
      
        
    471. 
          
          
                    captured_stdout, captured_stderr = Tempfile.new("out"), Tempfile.new("err")
        
      472. 
      
        
    472. 
          
          
          
        
      473. 
      
        
    473. 
          
          
                    orig_stdout, orig_stderr = $stdout.dup, $stderr.dup
        
      474. 
      
        
    474. 
          
          
                    $stdout.reopen captured_stdout
        
      475. 
      
        
    475. 
          
          
                    $stderr.reopen captured_stderr
        
      476. 
      
        
    476. 
          
          
          
        
      477. 
      
        
    477. 
          
          
                    yield
        
      478. 
      
        
    478. 
          
          
          
        
      479. 
      
        
    479. 
          
          
                    $stdout.rewind
        
      480. 
      
        
    480. 
          
          
                    $stderr.rewind
        
      481. 
      
        
    481. 
          
          
          
        
      482. 
      
        
    482. 
          
          
                    return captured_stdout.read, captured_stderr.read
        
      483. 
      
        
    483. 
          
          
                  ensure
        
      484. 
      
        
    484. 
          
          
                    captured_stdout.unlink
        
      485. 
      
        
    485. 
          
          
                    captured_stderr.unlink
        
      486. 
      
        
    486. 
          
          
                    $stdout.reopen orig_stdout
        
      487. 
      
        
    487. 
          
          
                    $stderr.reopen orig_stderr
        
      488. 
      
        
    488. 
          
          
                  end
        
      489. 
      
        
    489. 
          
          
                end
        
      490. 
      
        
    490. 
          
          
              end
        
      491. 
      
        
    491. 
          
          
          
        
      492. 
      
        
    492. 
          
          
              ##
        
      493. 
      
        
    493. 
          
          
              # Returns details for exception +e+
        
      494. 
      
        
    494. 
          
          
          
        
      495. 
      
        
    495. 
          1
          
              def exception_details e, msg
        
      496. 
      
        
    496. 
          
          
                [
        
      497. 
      
        
    497. 
          
          
                 "#{msg}",
        
      498. 
      
        
    498. 
          
          
                 "Class: <#{e.class}>",
        
      499. 
      
        
    499. 
          
          
                 "Message: <#{e.message.inspect}>",
        
      500. 
      
        
    500. 
          
          
                 "---Backtrace---",
        
      501. 
      
        
    501. 
          
          
                 "#{Minitest.filter_backtrace(e.backtrace).join("\n")}",
        
      502. 
      
        
    502. 
          
          
                 "---------------",
        
      503. 
      
        
    503. 
          
          
                ].join "\n"
        
      504. 
      
        
    504. 
          
          
              end
        
      505. 
      
        
    505. 
          
          
          
        
      506. 
      
        
    506. 
          
          
              ##
        
      507. 
      
        
    507. 
          
          
              # Fails with +msg+
        
      508. 
      
        
    508. 
          
          
          
        
      509. 
      
        
    509. 
          1
          
              def flunk msg = nil
        
      510. 
      
        
    510. 
          
          
                msg ||= "Epic Fail!"
        
      511. 
      
        
    511. 
          
          
                assert false, msg
        
      512. 
      
        
    512. 
          
          
              end
        
      513. 
      
        
    513. 
          
          
          
        
      514. 
      
        
    514. 
          
          
              ##
        
      515. 
      
        
    515. 
          
          
              # Returns a proc that will output +msg+ along with the default message.
        
      516. 
      
        
    516. 
          
          
          
        
      517. 
      
        
    517. 
          1
          
              def message msg = nil, ending = nil, &default
        
      518. 
      
        
    518. 
          1
          
                proc {
        
      519. 
      
        
    519. 
          
          
                  msg = msg.call.chomp(".") if Proc === msg
        
      520. 
      
        
    520. 
          
          
                  custom_message = "#{msg}.\n" unless msg.nil? or msg.to_s.empty?
        
      521. 
      
        
    521. 
          
          
                  "#{custom_message}#{default.call}#{ending || "."}"
        
      522. 
      
        
    522. 
          
          
                }
        
      523. 
      
        
    523. 
          
          
              end
        
      524. 
      
        
    524. 
          
          
          
        
      525. 
      
        
    525. 
          
          
              ##
        
      526. 
      
        
    526. 
          
          
              # used for counting assertions
        
      527. 
      
        
    527. 
          
          
          
        
      528. 
      
        
    528. 
          1
          
              def pass _msg = nil
        
      529. 
      
        
    529. 
          
          
                assert true
        
      530. 
      
        
    530. 
          
          
              end
        
      531. 
      
        
    531. 
          
          
          
        
      532. 
      
        
    532. 
          
          
              ##
        
      533. 
      
        
    533. 
          
          
              # Fails if +test+ is truthy.
        
      534. 
      
        
    534. 
          
          
          
        
      535. 
      
        
    535. 
          1
          
              def refute test, msg = nil
        
      536. 
      
        
    536. 
          
          
                msg ||= message { "Expected #{mu_pp(test)} to not be truthy" }
        
      537. 
      
        
    537. 
          
          
                not assert !test, msg
        
      538. 
      
        
    538. 
          
          
              end
        
      539. 
      
        
    539. 
          
          
          
        
      540. 
      
        
    540. 
          
          
              ##
        
      541. 
      
        
    541. 
          
          
              # Fails if +obj+ is empty.
        
      542. 
      
        
    542. 
          
          
          
        
      543. 
      
        
    543. 
          1
          
              def refute_empty obj, msg = nil
        
      544. 
      
        
    544. 
          
          
                msg = message(msg) { "Expected #{mu_pp(obj)} to not be empty" }
        
      545. 
      
        
    545. 
          
          
                assert_respond_to obj, :empty?
        
      546. 
      
        
    546. 
          
          
                refute obj.empty?, msg
        
      547. 
      
        
    547. 
          
          
              end
        
      548. 
      
        
    548. 
          
          
          
        
      549. 
      
        
    549. 
          
          
              ##
        
      550. 
      
        
    550. 
          
          
              # Fails if <tt>exp == act</tt>.
        
      551. 
      
        
    551. 
          
          
              #
        
      552. 
      
        
    552. 
          
          
              # For floats use refute_in_delta.
        
      553. 
      
        
    553. 
          
          
          
        
      554. 
      
        
    554. 
          1
          
              def refute_equal exp, act, msg = nil
        
      555. 
      
        
    555. 
          
          
                msg = message(msg) {
        
      556. 
      
        
    556. 
          
          
                  "Expected #{mu_pp(act)} to not be equal to #{mu_pp(exp)}"
        
      557. 
      
        
    557. 
          
          
                }
        
      558. 
      
        
    558. 
          
          
                refute exp == act, msg
        
      559. 
      
        
    559. 
          
          
              end
        
      560. 
      
        
    560. 
          
          
          
        
      561. 
      
        
    561. 
          
          
              ##
        
      562. 
      
        
    562. 
          
          
              # For comparing Floats.  Fails if +exp+ is within +delta+ of +act+.
        
      563. 
      
        
    563. 
          
          
              #
        
      564. 
      
        
    564. 
          
          
              #   refute_in_delta Math::PI, (22.0 / 7.0)
        
      565. 
      
        
    565. 
          
          
          
        
      566. 
      
        
    566. 
          1
          
              def refute_in_delta exp, act, delta = 0.001, msg = nil
        
      567. 
      
        
    567. 
          
          
                n = (exp - act).abs
        
      568. 
      
        
    568. 
          
          
                msg = message(msg) {
        
      569. 
      
        
    569. 
          
          
                  "Expected |#{exp} - #{act}| (#{n}) to not be <= #{delta}"
        
      570. 
      
        
    570. 
          
          
                }
        
      571. 
      
        
    571. 
          
          
                refute delta >= n, msg
        
      572. 
      
        
    572. 
          
          
              end
        
      573. 
      
        
    573. 
          
          
          
        
      574. 
      
        
    574. 
          
          
              ##
        
      575. 
      
        
    575. 
          
          
              # For comparing Floats.  Fails if +exp+ and +act+ have a relative error
        
      576. 
      
        
    576. 
          
          
              # less than +epsilon+.
        
      577. 
      
        
    577. 
          
          
          
        
      578. 
      
        
    578. 
          1
          
              def refute_in_epsilon a, b, epsilon = 0.001, msg = nil
        
      579. 
      
        
    579. 
          
          
                refute_in_delta a, b, a * epsilon, msg
        
      580. 
      
        
    580. 
          
          
              end
        
      581. 
      
        
    581. 
          
          
          
        
      582. 
      
        
    582. 
          
          
              ##
        
      583. 
      
        
    583. 
          
          
              # Fails if +collection+ includes +obj+.
        
      584. 
      
        
    584. 
          
          
          
        
      585. 
      
        
    585. 
          1
          
              def refute_includes collection, obj, msg = nil
        
      586. 
      
        
    586. 
          
          
                msg = message(msg) {
        
      587. 
      
        
    587. 
          
          
                  "Expected #{mu_pp(collection)} to not include #{mu_pp(obj)}"
        
      588. 
      
        
    588. 
          
          
                }
        
      589. 
      
        
    589. 
          
          
                assert_respond_to collection, :include?
        
      590. 
      
        
    590. 
          
          
                refute collection.include?(obj), msg
        
      591. 
      
        
    591. 
          
          
              end
        
      592. 
      
        
    592. 
          
          
          
        
      593. 
      
        
    593. 
          
          
              ##
        
      594. 
      
        
    594. 
          
          
              # Fails if +obj+ is an instance of +cls+.
        
      595. 
      
        
    595. 
          
          
          
        
      596. 
      
        
    596. 
          1
          
              def refute_instance_of cls, obj, msg = nil
        
      597. 
      
        
    597. 
          
          
                msg = message(msg) {
        
      598. 
      
        
    598. 
          
          
                  "Expected #{mu_pp(obj)} to not be an instance of #{cls}"
        
      599. 
      
        
    599. 
          
          
                }
        
      600. 
      
        
    600. 
          
          
                refute obj.instance_of?(cls), msg
        
      601. 
      
        
    601. 
          
          
              end
        
      602. 
      
        
    602. 
          
          
          
        
      603. 
      
        
    603. 
          
          
              ##
        
      604. 
      
        
    604. 
          
          
              # Fails if +obj+ is a kind of +cls+.
        
      605. 
      
        
    605. 
          
          
          
        
      606. 
      
        
    606. 
          1
          
              def refute_kind_of cls, obj, msg = nil
        
      607. 
      
        
    607. 
          
          
                msg = message(msg) { "Expected #{mu_pp(obj)} to not be a kind of #{cls}" }
        
      608. 
      
        
    608. 
          
          
                refute obj.kind_of?(cls), msg
        
      609. 
      
        
    609. 
          
          
              end
        
      610. 
      
        
    610. 
          
          
          
        
      611. 
      
        
    611. 
          
          
              ##
        
      612. 
      
        
    612. 
          
          
              # Fails if +matcher+ <tt>=~</tt> +obj+.
        
      613. 
      
        
    613. 
          
          
          
        
      614. 
      
        
    614. 
          1
          
              def refute_match matcher, obj, msg = nil
        
      615. 
      
        
    615. 
          
          
                msg = message(msg) { "Expected #{mu_pp matcher} to not match #{mu_pp obj}" }
        
      616. 
      
        
    616. 
          
          
                assert_respond_to matcher, :"=~"
        
      617. 
      
        
    617. 
          
          
                matcher = Regexp.new Regexp.escape matcher if String === matcher
        
      618. 
      
        
    618. 
          
          
                refute matcher =~ obj, msg
        
      619. 
      
        
    619. 
          
          
              end
        
      620. 
      
        
    620. 
          
          
          
        
      621. 
      
        
    621. 
          
          
              ##
        
      622. 
      
        
    622. 
          
          
              # Fails if +obj+ is nil.
        
      623. 
      
        
    623. 
          
          
          
        
      624. 
      
        
    624. 
          1
          
              def refute_nil obj, msg = nil
        
      625. 
      
        
    625. 
          
          
                msg = message(msg) { "Expected #{mu_pp(obj)} to not be nil" }
        
      626. 
      
        
    626. 
          
          
                refute obj.nil?, msg
        
      627. 
      
        
    627. 
          
          
              end
        
      628. 
      
        
    628. 
          
          
          
        
      629. 
      
        
    629. 
          
          
              ##
        
      630. 
      
        
    630. 
          
          
              # Fails if +o1+ is not +op+ +o2+. Eg:
        
      631. 
      
        
    631. 
          
          
              #
        
      632. 
      
        
    632. 
          
          
              #   refute_operator 1, :>, 2 #=> pass
        
      633. 
      
        
    633. 
          
          
              #   refute_operator 1, :<, 2 #=> fail
        
      634. 
      
        
    634. 
          
          
          
        
      635. 
      
        
    635. 
          1
          
              def refute_operator o1, op, o2 = UNDEFINED, msg = nil
        
      636. 
      
        
    636. 
          
          
                return refute_predicate o1, op, msg if UNDEFINED == o2
        
      637. 
      
        
    637. 
          
          
                msg = message(msg) { "Expected #{mu_pp(o1)} to not be #{op} #{mu_pp(o2)}" }
        
      638. 
      
        
    638. 
          
          
                refute o1.__send__(op, o2), msg
        
      639. 
      
        
    639. 
          
          
              end
        
      640. 
      
        
    640. 
          
          
          
        
      641. 
      
        
    641. 
          
          
              ##
        
      642. 
      
        
    642. 
          
          
              # For testing with predicates.
        
      643. 
      
        
    643. 
          
          
              #
        
      644. 
      
        
    644. 
          
          
              #   refute_predicate str, :empty?
        
      645. 
      
        
    645. 
          
          
              #
        
      646. 
      
        
    646. 
          
          
              # This is really meant for specs and is front-ended by refute_operator:
        
      647. 
      
        
    647. 
          
          
              #
        
      648. 
      
        
    648. 
          
          
              #   str.wont_be :empty?
        
      649. 
      
        
    649. 
          
          
          
        
      650. 
      
        
    650. 
          1
          
              def refute_predicate o1, op, msg = nil
        
      651. 
      
        
    651. 
          
          
                msg = message(msg) { "Expected #{mu_pp(o1)} to not be #{op}" }
        
      652.

                refute o1.__send__(op), msg
        
      653. 
      
        
    653.

      7.

      17. 
      
        
    17. 
          
          
                  case
        
      18. 
      
        
    18. 
          
          
                  when #{!!dont_flip} then
        
      19. 
      
        
    19. 
          
          
                    ctx.#{meth}(target, *args)
        
      20. 
      
        
    20. 
          
          
                  when #{block} && Proc === target then
        
      21. 
      
        
    21. 
          
          
                    ctx.#{meth}(*args, &target)
        
      22. 
      
        
    22. 
          
          
                  else
        
      23. 
      
        
    23. 
          
          
                    ctx.#{meth}(args.first, target, *args[1..-1])
        
      24. 
      
        
    24. 
          
          
                  end
        
      25. 
      
        
    25. 
          
          
                end
        
      26. 
      
        
    26. 
          
          
              EOM
        
      27. 
      
        
    27. 
          
          
            end
        
      28. 
      
        
    28. 
          
          
          end

    37. 
          
          
            # Describe a series of expectations for a given target +desc+.

    39. 
          
          
            # Defines a test class subclassing from either Minitest::Spec or
        
      40. 
      
        
    40. 
          
          
            # from the surrounding describe's class. The surrounding class may
        
      41. 
      
        
    41. 
          
          
            # subclass Minitest::Spec manually in order to easily share code:
        
      42. 
      
        
    42.

            #     class MySpec < Minitest::Spec
        
      44. 
      
        
    44.

      45. 
      
        
    45. 
          
          
            #     end
        
      46. 
      
        
    46. 
          
          
            #
        
      47. 
      
        
    47. 
          
          
            #     class TestStuff < MySpec
        
      48. 
      
        
    48. 
          
          
            #       it "does stuff" do
        
      49. 
      
        
    49. 
          
          
            #         # shared code available here
        
      50. 
      
        
    50. 
          
          
            #       end
        
      51. 
      
        
    51. 
          
          
            #       describe "inner stuff" do
        
      52. 
      
        
    52.

      53. 
      
        
    53. 
          
          
            #           # ...and here
        
      54. 
      
        
    54. 
          
          
            #         end
        
      55. 
      
        
    55. 
          
          
            #       end
        
      56. 
      
        
    56. 
          
          
            #     end
        
      57. 
      
        
    57. 
          
          
            #
        
      58.

            # For more information on getting started with writing specs, see:
        
      59. 
      
        
    59. 
          
          
            #
        
      60. 
      
        
    60. 
          
          
            # http://www.rubyinside.com/a-minitestspec-tutorial-elegant-spec-style-testing-that-comes-with-ruby-5354.html
        
      61. 
      
        
    61. 
          
          
            #
        
      62. 
      
        
    62. 
          
          
            # For some suggestions on how to improve your specs, try:
        
      63. 
      
        
    63. 
          
          
            #
        
      64. 
      
        
    64. 
          
          
            # http://betterspecs.org
        
      65. 
      
        
    65. 
          
          
            #
        
      66. 
      
        
    66. 
          
          
            # but do note that several items there are debatable or specific to
        
      67.

            # rspec.

            def describe desc, *additional_desc, &block # :doc:
        
      72. 
      
        
    72. 
          
          
              stack = Minitest::Spec.describe_stack
        
      73. 
      
        
    73. 
          
          
              name  = [stack.last, desc, *additional_desc].compact.join("::")
        
      74. 
      
        
    74. 
          
          
              sclas = stack.last || if Class === self && kind_of?(Minitest::Spec::DSL) then
        
      75. 
      
        
    75. 
          
          
                                      self
        
      76. 
      
        
    76. 
          
          
                                    else
        
      77. 
      
        
    77. 
          
          
                                      Minitest::Spec.spec_type desc, *additional_desc
        
      78. 
      
        
    78. 
          
          
                                    end
        
      79. 
      
        
    79. 
          
          
          
        
      80. 
      
        
    80. 
          
          
              cls = sclas.create name, desc
        
      81. 
      
        
    81. 
          
          
          
        
      82. 
      
        
    82. 
          
          
              stack.push cls
        
      83. 
      
        
    83. 
          
          
              cls.class_eval(&block)
        
      84. 
      
        
    84. 
          
          
              stack.pop
        
      85. 
      
        
    85. 
          
          
              cls
        
      86. 
      
        
    86. 
          
          
            end

            module DSL

              ##
        
      111. 
      
        
    111. 
          
          
              # Contains pairs of matchers and Spec classes to be used to
        
      112. 
      
        
    112. 
          
          
              # calculate the superclass of a top-level describe. This allows for
        
      113. 
      
        
    113. 
          
          
              # automatically customizable spec types.
        
      114.

              #
        
      115.

          1
          
              TYPES = [[//, Minitest::Spec]]
        
      118. 
      
        
    118. 
          
          
          
        
      119. 
      
        
    119. 
          
          
              ##
        
      120. 
      
        
    120. 
          
          
              # Register a new type of spec that matches the spec's description.
        
      121. 
      
        
    121. 
          
          
              # This method can take either a Regexp and a spec class or a spec
        
      122. 
      
        
    122. 
          
          
              # class and a block that takes the description and returns true if
        
      123. 
      
        
    123. 
          
          
              # it matches.
        
      124. 
      
        
    124. 
          
          
              #
        
      125. 
      
        
    125. 
          
          
              # Eg:
        
      126. 
      
        
    126. 
          
          
              #
        
      127. 
      
        
    127. 
          
          
              #     register_spec_type(/Controller$/, Minitest::Spec::Rails)
        
      128. 
      
        
    128. 
          
          
              #
        
      129. 
      
        
    129. 
          
          
              # or:
        
      130. 
      
        
    130. 
          
          
              #
        
      131. 
      
        
    131. 
          
          
              #     register_spec_type(Minitest::Spec::RailsModel) do |desc|
        
      132. 
      
        
    132. 
          
          
              #       desc.superclass == ActiveRecord::Base
        
      133. 
      
        
    133. 
          
          
              #     end
        
      134. 
      
        
    134.

              def register_spec_type *args, &block
        
      136. 
      
        
    136. 
          
          
                if block then
        
      137. 
      
        
    137. 
          
          
                  matcher, klass = block, args.first
        
      138. 
      
        
    138. 
          
          
                else
        
      139. 
      
        
    139. 
          
          
                  matcher, klass = *args
        
      140. 
      
        
    140. 
          
          
                end
        
      141. 
      
        
    141. 
          
          
                TYPES.unshift [matcher, klass]
        
      142. 
      
        
    142. 
          
          
              end
        
      143. 
      
        
    143. 
          
          
          
        
      144. 
      
        
    144. 
          
          
              ##
        
      145. 
      
        
    145. 
          
          
              # Figure out the spec class to use based on a spec's description. Eg:
        
      146. 
      
        
    146. 
          
          
              #
        
      147. 
      
        
    147. 
          
          
              #     spec_type("BlahController") # => Minitest::Spec::Rails
        
      148. 
      
        
    148. 
          
          
          
        
      149. 
      
        
    149. 
          1
          
              def spec_type desc, *additional
        
      150. 
      
        
    150. 
          
          
                TYPES.find { |matcher, _klass|
        
      151. 
      
        
    151. 
          
          
                  if matcher.respond_to? :call then
        
      152. 
      
        
    152. 
          
          
                    matcher.call desc, *additional
        
      153. 
      
        
    153. 
          
          
                  else
        
      154. 
      
        
    154. 
          
          
                    matcher === desc.to_s
        
      155. 
      
        
    155. 
          
          
                  end
        
      156. 
      
        
    156. 
          
          
                }.last
        
      157. 
      
        
    157. 
          
          
              end
        
      158. 
      
        
    158. 
          
          
          
        
      159. 
      
        
    159. 
          1
          
              def describe_stack # :nodoc:
        
      160.

                Thread.current[:describe_stack] ||= []
        
      161. 
      
        
    161. 
          
          
              end

                @children ||= []

              def nuke_test_methods! # :nodoc:

                end

              ##
        
      174. 
      
        
    174. 
          
          
              # Define a 'before' action. Inherits the way normal methods should.
        
      175. 
      
        
    175. 
          
          
              #

    177.

                define_method :setup do
        
      182. 
      
        
    182. 
          
          
                  super()
        
      183. 
      
        
    183. 
          
          
                  self.instance_eval(&block)
        
      184. 
      
        
    184. 
          
          
                end
        
      185.

              end

      188. 
      
        
    188. 
          
          
              # Define an 'after' action. Inherits the way normal methods should.
        
      189. 
      
        
    189. 
          
          
              #
        
      190. 
      
        
    190. 
          
          
              # NOTE: +type+ is ignored and is only there to make porting easier.
        
      191.

                  self.instance_eval(&block)

                end

      201. 
      
        
    201. 
          
          
              ##
        
      202. 
      
        
    202. 
          
          
              # Define an expectation with name +desc+. Name gets morphed to a
        
      203. 
      
        
    203. 
          
          
              # proper test method name. For some freakish reason, people who
        
      204. 
      
        
    204. 
          
          
              # write specs don't like class inheritance, so this goes way out of
        
      205. 
      
        
    205. 
          
          
              # its way to make sure that expectations aren't inherited.
        
      206. 
      
        
    206. 
          
          
              #
        
      207. 
      
        
    207. 
          
          
              # This is also aliased to #specify and doesn't require a +desc+ arg.
        
      208. 
      
        
    208. 
          
          
              #
        
      209. 
      
        
    209. 
          
          
              # Hint: If you _do_ want inheritance, use minitest/test. You can mix
        
      210. 
      
        
    210. 
          
          
              # and match between assertions and expectations as much as you want.
        
      211. 
      
        
    211. 
          
          
          
        
      212. 
      
        
    212. 
          1
          
              def it desc = "anonymous", &block
        
      213. 
      
        
    213. 
          
          
                block ||= proc { skip "(no tests defined)" }
        
      214. 
      
        
    214. 
          
          
          
        
      215. 
      
        
    215. 
          
          
                @specs ||= 0
        
      216. 
      
        
    216. 
          
          
                @specs += 1
        
      217. 
      
        
    217. 
          
          
          
        
      218. 
      
        
    218. 
          
          
                name = "test_%04d_%s" % [ @specs, desc ]
        
      219. 
      
        
    219. 
          
          
          
        
      220. 
      
        
    220. 
          
          
                undef_klasses = self.children.reject { |c| c.public_method_defined? name }
        
      221. 
      
        
    221. 
          
          
          
        
      222. 
      
        
    222. 
          
          
                define_method name, &block
        
      223. 
      
        
    223. 
          
          
          
        
      224. 
      
        
    224. 
          
          
                undef_klasses.each do |undef_klass|
        
      225. 
      
        
    225. 
          
          
                  undef_klass.send :undef_method, name
        
      226. 
      
        
    226. 
          
          
                end
        
      227. 
      
        
    227. 
          
          
          
        
      228. 
      
        
    228. 
          
          
                name
        
      229. 
      
        
    229. 
          
          
              end

      231.

              ##
        
      232. 
      
        
    232. 
          
          
              # Essentially, define an accessor for +name+ with +block+.
        
      233. 
      
        
    233. 
          
          
              #
        
      234. 
      
        
    234. 
          
          
              # Why use let instead of def? I honestly don't know.
        
      235.

      236. 
      
        
    236. 
          1
          
              def let name, &block
        
      237. 
      
        
    237. 
          
          
                name = name.to_s
        
      238. 
      
        
    238. 
          
          
                pre, post = "let '#{name}' cannot ", ". Please use another name."
        
      239. 
      
        
    239. 
          
          
                methods = Minitest::Spec.instance_methods.map(&:to_s) - %w[subject]
        
      240. 
      
        
    240. 
          
          
                raise ArgumentError, "#{pre}begin with 'test'#{post}" if
        
      241. 
      
        
    241. 
          
          
                  name =~ /\Atest/
        
      242. 
      
        
    242. 
          
          
                raise ArgumentError, "#{pre}override a method in Minitest::Spec#{post}" if
        
      243. 
      
        
    243. 
          
          
                  methods.include? name
        
      244. 
      
        
    244. 
          
          
          
        
      245. 
      
        
    245. 
          
          
                define_method name do
        
      246. 
      
        
    246. 
          
          
                  @_memoized ||= {}
        
      247. 
      
        
    247. 
          
          
                  @_memoized.fetch(name) { |k| @_memoized[k] = instance_eval(&block) }
        
      248. 
      
        
    248. 
          
          
                end
        
      249. 
      
        
    249. 
          
          
              end
        
      250. 
      
        
    250. 
          
          
          
        
      251. 
      
        
    251. 
          
          
              ##
        
      252. 
      
        
    252. 
          
          
              # Another lazy man's accessor generator. Made even more lazy by
        
      253. 
      
        
    253. 
          
          
              # setting the name for you to +subject+.

              def subject &block

              end

                children << cls
        
      268.

    270.

                name # Can't alias due to 1.8.7, not sure why

      285.

    286. 
          1
          
              module InstanceMethods
        
      287. 
      
        
    287. 
          
          
                ##
        
      288. 
      
        
    288. 
          
          
                # Returns a value monad that has all of Expectations methods
        
      289. 
      
        
    289. 
          
          
                # available to it.
        
      290. 
      
        
    290. 
          
          
                #
        
      291. 
      
        
    291. 
          
          
                # Also aliased to #value and #expect for your aesthetic pleasure:
        
      292. 
      
        
    292. 
          
          
                #
        
      293. 
      
        
    293. 
          
          
                #         _(1 + 1).must_equal 2

              # Render a Cookie HTTP request header from the contents of the @cookie_jar,
        
      238.

      239.

      244.

          1
          
              def make_cookie_header
        
      245.

          1
          
                return nil if cookie_jar.nil?
        
      246. 
      
        
    246. 
          
          
          
        
      247.

          1

      251. 
      
        
    251. 
          
          
              end
        
      252. 
      
        
    252. 
          
          
          
        
      253. 
      
        
    253. 
          
          
              # Process cookies passed as hash or as HTTP::CookieJar. For backwards
        
      254. 
      
        
    254. 
          
          
              # compatibility, these may be passed as a :cookies option masquerading
        
      255. 
      
        
    255. 
          
          
              # inside the headers hash. To avoid confusion, if :cookies is passed in
        
      256. 
      
        
    256. 
          
          
              # both headers and Request#initialize, raise an error.
        
      257. 
      
        
    257. 
          
          
              #
        
      258. 
      
        
    258. 
          
          
              # :cookies may be a:
        
      259. 
      
        
    259. 
          
          
              # - Hash{String/Symbol => String}
        
      260. 
      
        
    260. 
          
          
              # - Array<HTTP::Cookie>
        
      261. 
      
        
    261. 
          
          
              # - HTTP::CookieJar
        
      262. 
      
        
    262. 
          
          
              #
        
      263. 
      
        
    263. 
          
          
              # Passing as a hash:
        
      264. 
      
        
    264. 
          
          
              #   Keys may be symbols or strings. Values must be strings.
        
      265. 
      
        
    265. 
          
          
              #   Infer the domain name from the request URI and allow subdomains (as
        
      266. 
      
        
    266. 
          
          
              #   though '.example.com' had been set in a Set-Cookie header). Assume a
        
      267. 
      
        
    267. 
          
          
              #   path of '/'.
        
      268. 
      
        
    268. 
          
          
              #
        
      269. 
      
        
    269. 
          
          
              #     RestClient::Request.new(url: 'http://example.com', method: :get,
        
      270. 
      
        
    270. 
          
          
              #       :cookies => {:foo => 'Value', 'bar' => '123'}
        
      271. 
      
        
    271. 
          
          
              #     )
        
      272. 
      
        
    272. 
          
          
              #
        
      273. 
      
        
    273. 
          
          
              # results in cookies as though set from the server by:
        
      274. 
      
        
    274. 
          
          
              #     Set-Cookie: foo=Value; Domain=.example.com; Path=/
        
      275. 
      
        
    275. 
          
          
              #     Set-Cookie: bar=123; Domain=.example.com; Path=/
        
      276. 
      
        
    276. 
          
          
              #
        
      277. 
      
        
    277. 
          
          
              # which yields a client cookie header of:
        
      278. 
      
        
    278. 
          
          
              #     Cookie: foo=Value; bar=123
        
      279. 
      
        
    279. 
          
          
              #
        
      280. 
      
        
    280. 
          
          
              # Passing as HTTP::CookieJar, which will be passed through directly:
        
      281. 
      
        
    281. 
          
          
              #
        
      282. 
      
        
    282. 
          
          
              #     jar = HTTP::CookieJar.new
        
      283. 
      
        
    283. 
          
          
              #     jar.add(HTTP::Cookie.new('foo', 'Value', domain: 'example.com',
        
      284. 
      
        
    284. 
          
          
              #                              path: '/', for_domain: false))
        
      285. 
      
        
    285. 
          
          
              #
        
      286. 
      
        
    286. 
          
          
              #     RestClient::Request.new(..., :cookies => jar)
        
      287. 
      
        
    287. 
          
          
              #
        
      288. 
      
        
    288. 
          
          
              # @param [URI::HTTP] uri The URI for the request. This will be used to
        
      289. 
      
        
    289. 
          
          
              # infer the domain name for cookies passed as strings in a hash. To avoid
        
      290. 
      
        
    290. 
          
          
              # this implicit behavior, pass a full cookie jar or use HTTP::Cookie hash
        
      291. 
      
        
    291. 
          
          
              # values.
        
      292. 
      
        
    292. 
          
          
              # @param [Hash] headers The headers hash from which to pull the :cookies
        
      293. 
      
        
    293. 
          
          
              #   option. MUTATION NOTE: This key will be deleted from the hash if
        
      294. 
      
        
    294. 
          
          
              #   present.
        
      295. 
      
        
    295. 
          
          
              # @param [Hash] args The options passed to Request#initialize. This hash
        
      296. 
      
        
    296. 
          
          
              #   will be used as another potential source for the :cookies key.
        
      297. 
      
        
    297. 
          
          
              #   These args will not be mutated.
        
      298. 
      
        
    298. 
          
          
              #
        
      299. 
      
        
    299.

              def setup_credentials(req)

              def fetch_body(http_response)
        
      769. 
      
        
    769. 
          1
          
                if @raw_response
        
      770. 
      
        
    770. 
          
          
                  # Taken from Chef, which as in turn...
        
      771. 
      
        
    771. 
          
          
                  # Stolen from http://www.ruby-forum.com/topic/166423
        
      772. 
      
        
    772. 
          
          
                  # Kudos to _why!
        
      773. 
      
        
    773. 
          
          
                  @tf = Tempfile.new('rest-client.')
        
      774. 
      
        
    774. 
          
          
                  @tf.binmode
        
      775. 
      
        
    775. 
          
          
                  size, total = 0, http_response['Content-Length'].to_i
        
      776. 
      
        
    776. 
          
          
                  http_response.read_body do |chunk|
        
      777. 
      
        
    777. 
          
          
                    @tf.write chunk
        
      778. 
      
        
    778. 
          
          
                    size += chunk.size
        
      779. 
      
        
    779. 
          
          
                    if RestClient.log
        
      780. 
      
        
    780. 
          
          
                      if size == 0
        
      781. 
      
        
    781. 
          
          
                        RestClient.log << "%s %s done (0 length file)\n" % [@method, @url]
        
      782. 
      
        
    782. 
          
          
                      elsif total == 0
        
      783. 
      
        
    783. 
          
          
                        RestClient.log << "%s %s (zero content length)\n" % [@method, @url]
        
      784. 
      
        
    784. 
          
          
                      else
        
      785. 
      
        
    785. 
          
          
                        RestClient.log << "%s %s %d%% done (%d of %d)\n" % [@method, @url, (size * 100) / total, size, total]
        
      786. 
      
        
    786. 
          
          
                      end
        
      787. 
      
        
    787. 
          
          
                    end
        
      788. 
      
        
    788. 
          
          
                  end
        
      789. 
      
        
    789.

      790. 
      
        
    790. 
          
          
                  @tf
        
      791. 
      
        
    791. 
          
          
                else
        
      792. 
      
        
    792. 
          1
          
                  http_response.read_body
        
      793. 
      
        
    793.

      794.

          1
          
                http_response
        
      795. 
      
        
    795.

              def process_result res, & block
        
      798.

          1
          
                if @raw_response
        
      799. 
      
        
    799. 
          
          
                  # We don't decode raw requests
        
      800. 
      
        
    800. 
          
          
                  response = RawResponse.new(@tf, res, self)
        
      801. 
      
        
    801.

      802.

          1
          
                  decoded = Request.decode(res['content-encoding'], res.body)

    803. 
          1

    810.

              def parser

      817. 
      
        
    817. 
          
          
          
        
      818. 
      
        
    818. 
          
          
              # Given a MIME type or file extension, return either a MIME type or, if
        
      819. 
      
        
    819. 
          
          
              # none is found, the input unchanged.
        
      820.

              #
        
      821. 
      
        
    821. 
          
          
              #     >> maybe_convert_extension('json')
        
      822. 
      
        
    822. 
          
          
              #     => 'application/json'
        
      823.

              #     >> maybe_convert_extension('unknown')
        
      825. 
      
        
    825. 
          
          
              #     => 'unknown'
        
      826. 
      
        
    826.
